{% comment %} iterates over each block in the section's blocks collection {% endcomment %}
{%- for block in section.blocks -%}
  {%- case block.type -%}
    {%- when 'announcement' -%}
      <div
        {% comment %} block er setting e dropdown select input type theke j option select kora hobe, shei option er value niye e.g: color-background-2 class toiri hobe. R style likha thakche css e. {% endcomment %}
        class="announcement-bar color-{{ block.settings.color_scheme }} gradient"
        role="region"
        {% comment %} sections is not an object or variable. Instead, it is part of a translation key string. Shopify uses translation files (locales) to store text in different languages. The key 'sections.header.announcement' refers to a specific entry in your locale files (like en.default.json). The | t filter tells Shopify to look up this key and output the translated text. {% endcomment %}
        aria-label="{{ 'sections.header.announcement' | t }}"

        {% comment %} When you use {{ block.shopify_attributes }} inside a block's HTML tag, Shopify automatically adds various data attributes (like data-block-id, etc.) that help the theme editor identify and interact with that specific block. These attributes are used by the Shopify theme editor to enable live editing, drag-and-drop, and other customization features. These attributes are not visible to regular visitors but are essential for the theme customization experience in the Shopify admin. {% endcomment %}
        {{ block.shopify_attributes }}
      >
        {% comment %} if text is not empty in the block {% endcomment %}
        {%- if block.settings.text != blank -%}
          {% comment %} if block has link, inject anchor tag {% endcomment %}
          {%- if block.settings.link != blank -%}
            <a
              href="{{ block.settings.link }}"
              class="announcement-bar__link link link--text focus-inset animate-arrow"
            >
          {%- endif -%}
          {% comment %} show block text content and arrow if link exists. The escape filter converts special characters in a string to their corresponding HTML entities. This prevents HTML tags or special characters from being interpreted as code, which helps protect against cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks and ensures that user-generated content is displayed safely as plain text. For example, < becomes &lt; and & becomes &amp; {% endcomment %}
          <p class="announcement-bar__message h5">
            {{ block.settings.text | escape }}
            {%- if block.settings.link != blank -%}
              {% render 'icon-arrow' %}
            {%- endif -%}
          </p>
          {%- if block.settings.link != blank -%}
            </a>
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
  {%- endcase -%}
{%- endfor -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "t:sections.announcement-bar.name",
  "max_blocks": 12,
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "announcement",
      "name": "t:sections.announcement-bar.blocks.announcement.name",
      "settings": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "text",
          "default": "Welcome to our store",
          "label": "t:sections.announcement-bar.blocks.announcement.settings.text.label"
        },
        {
          "type": "select",
          "id": "color_scheme",
          "default": "accent-1",
          "label": "t:sections.announcement-bar.blocks.announcement.settings.color_scheme.label",
          "options": [
            {
              "value": "background-1",
              "label": "t:sections.announcement-bar.blocks.announcement.settings.color_scheme.options__1.label"
            },
            {
              "value": "background-2",
              "label": "t:sections.announcement-bar.blocks.announcement.settings.color_scheme.options__2.label"
            },
            {
              "value": "inverse",
              "label": "t:sections.announcement-bar.blocks.announcement.settings.color_scheme.options__3.label"
            },
            {
              "value": "accent-1",
              "label": "t:sections.announcement-bar.blocks.announcement.settings.color_scheme.options__4.label"
            },
            {
              "value": "accent-2",
              "label": "t:sections.announcement-bar.blocks.announcement.settings.color_scheme.options__5.label"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "url",
          "id": "link",
          "label": "t:sections.announcement-bar.blocks.announcement.settings.link.label"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "default": {
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "announcement"
      }
    ]
  }
}
{% endschema %}

{% comment %}
  this section can have up to 12 announcement blocks. Each block is of type "announcement" and includes several
  customizable settings: "text": the merchant can enter the announcement message. It has a default value of "Welcome to our store" and a translatable label.
  "color_scheme": A dropdown (select) allowing the merchant to choose from several color schemes (like background-1, background-2, inverse, accent-1, accent-2). Each option has a value and a translatable label. The default is "accent-1".
  "link": A URL field where the merchant can provide a link for the announcement, making
  the message clickable.

  The "default" property ensures that when the section is first added, it starts with one
  announcement block by default.

  All labels use translation keys, so the theme can support multiple languages.
{% endcomment %}
